    Hi! <br />I don't think he leaves but he is expelled. Alex takes control of the situation, has accepted him and is capable of confront his father. IU think he doesn't daydream anymore and accepts the situation as it is. Alex could quit or could stay and make his father go away... He is brave (maybe the first man of his family) enough to make a decission and confront it. Well, that's what I thought<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
